The Cleveland Metropolitan School District is the largest K–12 district in the state of Ohio, with 127 schools and an enrollment of 55,567 students during the 2006–2007 academic year.[170] It is the only district in Ohio that is under direct control of the mayor, who appoints a school board.[171]
